reviews:
i absolutely love this! i have two of these in my cupboards and it has saved us a tone of horizontal space which we have very little of.
i have one to hold half sheets pans and a cast iron grill. i have another one to hold frying pans.
it takes absolutely no time to set it up, the spacers are super easy to 'instal,' and move around to fit varying sized items. It does feel a bit flimsy but it holds a cast iron skillet in one of the slots and i haven't had any tipping issues and no issue with movement.
it's a necessity for small spaces.

im typically an xs/s so i ordered these in a small. i believe they're meant to fit low in the front, just barely covering the front bits. however, these were really low in the back as well. they could barely reach high enough in the back above my cheeks so it looks a bit unflattering. i should've ordered a medium.

im glad that products like these are now available for cheap through amazon!
my concern was that the hooks would not be sturdy enough and and it would bend out of shape from opening doors - other similar products had reviews like this.
im happy to say that these are sturdy and get the job done.

the items arrived on schedule and in perfect condition.
these were a gift to my family because I already have a pair and needed to buy these for everyone I know!
they are super handy and everyone in Asia has these hanging in their car for a reason.
this particular set is the most 'bang for your buck.' it comes with the two large double hangers but also four of the smaller hooks. both are great to have for the various items you may want to hang. I use these to transport soupy take-out and wet things that I don't want to have toppled over in my car and make a mess... (precious cargo like your BBT). installation... i wouldn't even call it that.. you simply hang it on the back of the headrest. done.

fits nicely, it's a little snug but it's fitting really well now.
i got both the black and the light grey.
taste great, exactly like you image it to be.

review_title: such a great investment! I bought it to hold my tech ...
reviews:
such a great investment!
I bought it to hold my tech gear when I am travelling or bring a lot of small accessories to work and want to stay organized. I was worried that it would be too small for my needs but it is perfect.

I am using it to hold my Sigma 52mm, lens cap, uv filter, batter pack, camera charger, iphone charger, apple headphones, and there is still a lot of space left. I want to get a travel adapter for an upcoming trip and it is going to fit into the extra space without issue.
Love this bag.

I have a mirrorless sony a6000 and i got this to hold my sigma 52mm. It fits in just right but could use just a smidge more coverage at the top as it won't close up fully. I bought this knowing it was a small and may not fit a 52mm so it's not a big deal.
It adds some cushioning around your lens to give you a piece of mind but you get what you pay for. I got it for $6.99 and it does the job so I am satisfied and will buy more for eventually.

this item is super useful.
I was apprehensive of the quality of the item because of the price points; it felt too good to be true.
I was pleasantly surprised at how nice this item feels. It is so lightweight and works great doing what it is intended to do.
I use it primarily for transferring images from my SD card and it's had no issue and I also not very careful with it and it's still holding up,
sour candy is great, this is great.

i got it when it went on sale which makes this purchase even better.
it works great and charges my phone at least 3 times.
the only con is that its heavy. there's definitely substantial weight from it when carrying it in my purse, but any power pack with a lot of juice ends up being weighty so it's not really an issue

i've had mine for over two months and it works great.
no connection issues and works perfectly fine.

this item is so convenient, i don't know why i didn't get one of these sooner.
the smaller round magnet holds my iphone 6 up without issue, it only flew off once when i had to break suddenly.
the larger rectangle magnet holds up my boyfriends shaomi A1 phone which has a thick case making it bulkier and heavier.
a great buy for it's price point considering the crappy ones that clip onto your phone are close in price but not as effective.

it does the job and is good for its price. I don't like that the bottom piece has to screw into the camera; it's bulky and uncomfortable to hold when using the camera.
i bought it to protect my camera when i carry it in my bag, i didn't want anything bulky and i needed it to be a bit sturdy. it does the job and the price is just right. it's a snug fit and won't fit anything more than the kit 16-50mm lens.

review_title: Works well and easy to apply
reviews:
Works well and easy to apply!
Comes in a cute box so that you can store the spare safely away. Easy to apply. I didn;t place it on perfectly the first time but it was easy to peel off and reapply..

review_title: Works great. These slide across the bar nice and smooth
reviews: Works great. These slide across the bar nice and smooth. It's great when I have to change the shower liner, I don't need to unhook the shower curtain as well. It's like weight does the job.
